Product data: {"item_id": 2108, "title": "Stanley - Coat of Arms, Crest & History 11x17 Print - Surname Origin: Ireland", "category": "raw_meta_Handmade_Products", "description": "The images used are EXAMPLES of what the product s will look like. This
COLLECTIBLE
product is a 11x17 print. The Surname for this product is the first word s in the products title and the country of origin is indicated with the last three words in the product title. This print uses the earliest coat of arms associated with a bearer of the surname last name and the time tested surname etymology, a history of the name and its origins throughout the ages. If available, it includes the ancient origin of the name, spelling variations, early movement of the surname during the Middle Ages, noteworthy bearers from around 1400AD or earlier up to current day, and first settlers in North America. There may be different variations of Coat of Arms for each surname and the one we use is the oldest registered Coat of Arms verified in history.
History of Heraldry 
Heraldry, in its broad meaning, traditionally had to do with the functions of a herald. Heraldry arose almost spontaneously in Medieval Europe around the 12th Century, coinciding with the development of armor, and the time of the crusades. This resulted in distinctive insignia s being painted on the knight s shield and embroidered on his surcoat, which was the only means by which the warrior could be identified.
The Perfect Gift 
These prints look great framed and or with matting! This product ships directly from the manufacturer so please contact us with any questions you may have prior to your purchase as changes after purchase are not possible. Can t find your name? Contact us along with the name you are interested in purchasing. Due to the nature of this product returns or exchanges are only granted if the product was damaged in transit.
Make sure to check out the variations abailable as well! The larger print offers more historical information then the smaller print.
Date First Available October 3, 2020", "price": 17.99}

Product data: {"item_id": 2119, "title": "Fraser (Saltoun) Clan Luckenbooth Brooch", "category": "raw_meta_Handmade_Products", "description": "SCOTTISH CLAN LUCKENBOOTH BROOCH
Your proud Scottish Clan heritage can be displayed with this beautiful Clan crest modern style Luckenbooth brooch. Each piece is exquisitely handcrafted in high detail in sterling silver, with your unique Clan crest. Every Scottish Clan is available.... over 300 Clan names! This stunning Clan Luckenbooth measures 1-7 16 36mm by 1-1 2 39mm with a high quality pin back. The Clan crest is 11 16 17mm in diameter. This Luckenbooth is also available as a pendant. This Luckenbooth can also be custom made in solid gold as well as a gold and sterling silver option. Just ask!. This stunning Luckenbooth features your Clan as the central emblem. A perfect piece to display your Scottish heritage or a lovely gift for your sweetheart. The Luckenbooth is one of the most romantic Scottish symbols of love, from the 17th century and often given as a token of betrothal, affection and friendship. It is usually in the shape of a heart or two entwined hearts, symbolizing love, with a crown, symbolizing loyalty n top of the heart for endless love.
Surprise her with one today!

The butterfly wing is set in a large vintage style antique silver setting with sparkling clear Swarovski crystals. The pendant measures 50x70mm and the chain comes in your choice of short 18 or long 28 . The Emperor Morpho Butterfly, also known as Morpho Peleides, is part of the Blue Morpho family and originates from Paraguay. The wings are a brilliant shimmering light blue with black edges. The color in the butterfly s wings is caused by the diffraction of the light from millions of tiny scales on its wings. It uses this to frighten away predators, by flashing its wings rapidly. The Emperor Morpho lives in the rainforest and drinks the juices from tropical fruit such as mango and kiwi. Each piece will arrive in its own organza gift bag or gift box with literature on the species of butterfly! NOTE My wings come from butterflies that have been raised on butterfly farms & conservatories and allowed to live their full lifespan, which naturally averages about 2-4 weeks and are then collected and preserved so that their beauty can live on! Butterfly Farming actually helps to preserve rain forests and also assures the survival of natural butterfly habitats. Native people are encouraged to grow plants and raise insects as opposed to clearing land for cash crops. Raising and selling insects is the only incentive many indigenous people have to save their tropical forests. I am proud to be a member of the RAINFOREST ALLIANCE! I support and donate to the Rainforest Alliance, a nonprofit organization dedicated to preserving the rainforest and the thousands of species living in it, including the Blue Morpho Butterfly!
